 lake which makes it super comfortable.\nIt‚Äôs a must visit if you are going with family or as a couple!!","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Romina Majidzadeh","rating":5,"text":"We discovered Grand Hotel Villa Castagnola by chance. We stopped by for some drinks and snacks, but were absolutely enchanted. We were warmly welcomed at the entrance, the drinks were excellent, and the stunning lake and lush greenery made it a peaceful, elegant, and unforgettable experience. I can‚Äôt wait to visit again! üå∏üèùÔ∏èü§©","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Noah Bernet","rating":5,"text":"The location, the view, the garden, and the exterior of the hotel are incredibly beautiful. Spending a summer evening in front of the hotel, accompanied by soft piano music and the stunning scenery, was truly unforgettable. The drinks were excellent, and another big plus was the late-night dining option, we ordered carbonara at 11 p.m., and it was served without any issue and the food was outstanding.\n---------\nHowever, the room and parts of the interior felt outdated. We stayed in a junior suite on the top floor, and while the view was again breathtaking, the room itself was not to our taste. The carpet and furniture were very old and did not reflect the standard of a five-star hotel. The service was fine but not exceptional, and the breakfast, while not bad, was also not particularly impressiv.\n---------\nWe will likely stay at the hotel again on our next weekend in Lugano, but only if refurbished rooms are available and we can be sure to book one of them. Breakfast, however, I would probably skip.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"bia pawlowski","rating":3,"text":"The rooms are nice but the hotel itself is dated. I was really confused by the spa... but the garden is nice and theres a private area to swim by the lake which is nice, but when we went there was a sign advising us not to swim in it. The hotel has potential but I wouldnt recommend the hotel tbh","time":"3 months ago"}]'::