ciated.\n\nWe booked our first-ever Michelin dinner at I Due Sud, and it was phenomenal. The food was stunningly delicious, the service was top-notch, and the head chef Marco came out to personally congratulate us on our honeymoon, including providing us several courses above and beyond our initial selections (even a happy honeymoon dessert!). All we could''ve asked for and more, I guarantee you will not leave hungry!\n\nI hope we''re one day lucky enough to return to Lugano. Until then, our warmest thanks and deepest appreciation to everyone at the Hotel Splendide Royal. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts for making our honeymoon such an unforgettable experience!","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Admin Admin","rating":2,"text":"Unfortunately, I cannot share many positive comments, except for the friendly welcome at the reception.\n\nDuring breakfast, the restaurant manager greeted only certain guests, visiting just two tables, while neither we nor other guests seated next to us were acknowledged.\nThis felt unusual and uncomfortable. The breakfast staff appeared rather reserved overall.\n\nWhile the location is excellent, that is unfortunately the only highlight.\n\nDue to our initial experience at breakfast and the room not being entirely satisfactory, we decided not to dine at the restaurant.","time":"in the last week"},{"author":"Tara Wilson","rating":5,"text":"We had such a lovely stay! The location is gorgeous, and easily walkable to many attractions in Lugano (although a bit farther from the main station). Everything about the stay was lovely, the rooms are comfortable and very clean and the staff was very friendly. The breakfast was delicious with many hot options, continental buffet and great coffee and we had a lovely dinner in the restaurant as well. We really enjoyed the spa relaxation room, sauna, and amazing view from the pool to relax in the winter!","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Mark Rosenthal","rating":5,"text":"This is an outstanding luxury property with some of the most incredible views over Lake Lugano you''ll find anywhere. The room was beautifully appointed with elegant furnishings and that bed was absolute perfection. The whole property has this timeless, sophisticated feel that manages to be luxurious without feeling pretentious. What really set this place apart was the staff, particularly our concierge who was always on point with recommendations and seemed to anticipate what we needed before we even knew what we wanted. The breakfast was excellent with high-quality options and beautiful presentation. Every detail felt carefully considered, from the room amenities to the public spaces. The view from our room was breathtaking and made even simple moments like morning coffee feel special. This is how luxury hospitality should be done - attentive service, beautiful setting, and genuine comfort. Would give 6 stars if that was an option, and we''d definitely return.","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
