N1ial_Amkgjy8mLY66ytq7JyFL38RNMVw4RG9_tj3ZqZuG6IOXcvP5oNF_-Tfzf0Q4oStIEWmJeoAPr_XYHn0wN5N7J8cnGfP_3-5vM_mlZSgOWintHuo0-mqb4L9IK2cZVfErKIq7IbUfDNSBP4nwaA-ypB8zDTTVr-tG6Z-gmisi_Oew-ESBZmGE3HODAN0BNWGgfm_5GSGuxLFwnfswxSIHYnXVdONipva1_6DxkOxfU1oY1y7X7rE5C3Q9Q-oDXv0T6Cji_m-w_Boh8iEnJBvjsZF4O-2e-nRIl9F0UBg","width":1024,"height":768,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/108174797537539285634\">Swiss Diamond Hotel Lake Lugano</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0C0eEnaoMYTg26KeZze1zl6xxTqvgqLNZdUT0CUx1bpF0NQWL1XfYvHc4HPTlKHElb2kwKSGvFn0KOVdUpFpFiPSU_CUX-Xlj1ADKJ88JHvRtWvPDHzON1fCrdtxjolJ2uebX8xbDOSs-kW0y2H1r8ffpSbmdPyqQsb0wNMzKw4e9ch8r_dwTBH1RXSE-z8hxxhMqfnVjr2h8WDdNXRzp7rGBj4kd_-FLBYJ3afnLFwfYR3IqxrXT64jTy8mEE7hYrakpHgmSwORCVEiVAC2iUtQVupEGhgur2mElrfZ_v1w","width":1024,"height":768,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/108174797537539285634\">Swiss Diamond Hotel Lake Lugano</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Lina Dehneh","rating":1,"text":"My family and I had a truly unpleasant experience at this hotel, which failed to meet even the most basic standards of service. We were lost just 15 minutes away from the property and requested assistance via their shuttle or a taxi‚Äîservices they claim to offer to all guests. Despite informing them that we had a 30-month-old child with us, it took over two hours and six phone calls before they finally sent a taxi. This delay caused unnecessary stress and discomfort for our family.\nThe staff were unhelpful and poorly informed. They lacked basic knowledge of the city and showed little interest in assisting guests.\n\nWe even spoke with the hotel owner, who introduced him self His attitude was equally disrespectful.and he was very rude and refused to talk about the situation.\nThe receptionist openly stated she didn‚Äôt care about what happened and continued to blame the taxi company, refusing to take any responsibility.\n\nInside the room, the amenities were shockingly minimal for a 5-star property. Only two basic Nescaf√© sachets were provided‚Äîno tea bags. If you enjoy a hot drink, you‚Äôre better off bringing your own. Additionally, the hotel is isolated, with no nearby supermarkets or restaurants, except for their own, which were underwhelming.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"vic NY (Vic NY)","rating":3,"text":"Don‚Äôt be misled by the hotel‚Äôs online photos of the lakefront. The main building actually sits across a busy road, separated from the lake. Only 4 rooms are directly on the lake, so if you pay extra for a ‚Äúlake view,‚Äù expect traffic noise and a parking lot in your line of sight. Ironically, the hotel‚Äôs parking lot has one of the best views, directly overlooking the lake. Unfortunately, there is no inviting indoor common area with a lake view for guests to enjoy. The most beautiful restaurant, which could easily serve that role, is closed most of the day‚Äîan opportunity the hotel really should rethink.\n\nThis property does not live up to 5-star standards. The interiors are outdated, in need of renovation, and the carpet in my room was badly stained, which felt unacceptable at this level.\n\nThe gardens and the main restaurant‚Äîheavily showcased on the website‚Äîare indeed lovely. However, guests cannot order food or snacks while sitting by the lake (apparently due to a local regulation). The restaurant with the best views serves only dinner, not breakfast. Breakfast is served on the street level with no view.  During the day, snacks are limited to the bar across the road, which is dark and dated. This fell far short of the relaxing holiday atmosphere I expected at lakeside. Wellness facilities were also disappointing: the sauna was out of order, the indoor pool is tiny and hidden away in the basement, and the outdoor pool was uncomfortably cold.\n\nThe one pleasant surprise was the complimentary shuttle to and from Morcote, a beautiful village where parking is very limited.\n\nBreakfast was mediocre‚Äîmore in line with a 4-star property. Fresh-squeezed orange juice and Parma ham were available, but only upon request. At this price point, those should be standard offerings for all guests.\n\nOverall, given the high rates and the actual experience, this hotel does not deliver on its 5-star promise, and I cannot recommend it.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Lach Falvey","rating":5,"text":"Spent 4 nights at the Swiss Diamond Hotel.\nIt was a fantastic experience.\n\nGiorgia & Davide\n( two waiters ) made our stay very comfortable and went out of there way every time we dined in the bar.\n\nThe hotel, location and view is breathtaking. Would happily recommend to anyone.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Hamish","rating":1,"text":"Stayed in May this year. It was perhaps very luxury a few years ago, but it needs a lot of work. Breakfast isn‚Äôt great, the restaurant brought out the wrong meal for my fiance - mistakes happen. But rather than offer to keep my food warm until hers was ready I was told I need to eat mine otherwise I will need to eat my dinner cold. Service generally pretty poor, not made to feel particularly welcome.\n\nThen, there was no air con in the room despite being advertised on booking.com as having air con. First night in the hotel I barely slept, 29 degrees C outside, similar inside. After a night of very little sleep I spoke to reception in the morning . I advised them that the air con did not work and that I needed air con in our room as it was very very hot. I was told the air con could not be switched on without consent from the neighbours. (Meanwhile there was aircon in reception), but because our complaint was not the first that weekend they would ‚Äúlook into it‚Äù\n\nWe were offered a very loud mobile aircon unit for our second night as a solution. So the room was somewhat cooler, but it was like sleeping near to a Boeing 747.\n\nOn exiting the hotel in expressed my disappointment with my stay, I was not prompted to ask how my stay was. I advised the property that despite having stayed in numerous 5 star hotels at a similar price point in Europe, I had been left very disappointed by this establishment.\n\nWe were offered a ‚Ç¨50 discount on a ‚Ç¨1100 stay and that there was no possibility of a further discount, unless we agreed to come back and stay again.\n\nSafe to say I will never return to this hotel. Poor service, overpriced, really disappointing","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Agatha Brand√£o de Oliveira","rating":3,"text":"We went for the day-spa pass and were a bit disappointed. While the website gives an impression that this could be a luxury spa, the infrastructure is dated and not well-taken care of (e.g., jacuzzi malfunctioning, dirty external pool, main sauna out of service, Turkish bath without anything). The internal pool area was very loud (there is no separate scheduled time for families with kids) and it is rather average. The showing/locker space is a bit confusing and not really convenient for external guests. The main highlight of the experience is the external sunbathing area, which is nice (beautiful lake view) but it is not very encouraging for swimming (i.e., complicated way to go in, no dedicated platform to stay in the lake). All in all, it‚Äôs not worth it.","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
