Fh5MdiQyVarwWsZb5cZZfbOrOCGwuzlZ6drukN0NCgDPDmt8i7eRJrIFL-4z7tQZIKmmyYkbQR3IFTD2E42Y-3sDBb3oye8GwWCGxck6O9ZEPg","width":4800,"height":3200,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/106460344225507794255\">Hotel Eden Roc Ascona</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0Sx7fC4iqptofTsZ92iiwNNHWAh3OzqFuM1Nc3e0YJSIpy-93nKIqXS11wPUXwbcSV7oyXTlNiKEHHn-GR4oELtF3D6Ps_LWZG8tHLmSybQHTG6iByIuVtrtZ6iDHK4zz7stYpfvP4Rx9d7NUdfDiW_MmIz5QlJ4l5FzSSL-wm1UJH3uZ305mX8HoM6mDJcQhOArd935Iu20YBA2S6ODvK1tp4_o7gJP925AwZVq1dG8FykMqFyXHjG7UTuMEcGKLjQyfTvRDFDPGnX0RxcgnRqDzZLCB2JS-ZXKEM9X-RkQ","width":1600,"height":1066,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/106460344225507794255\">Hotel Eden Roc Ascona</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Ben Greenstein","rating":5,"text":"My wife and I just returned from three unforgettable days at the Eden Roc in Ascona for our babymoon, and it truly exceeded every expectation. From the moment we arrived, the staff was warm, professional, and always a step ahead in making us feel cared for. The property is spotless, beautifully maintained, and perched right on Lake Maggiore with some of the most breathtaking views we‚Äôve ever seen.\n\nThe spa is world-class, the pools and private beach are pristine, and our room was kept in perfect condition with thoughtful touches that made us feel pampered. And the breakfast? Absolutely sick ‚Äî one of the best we‚Äôve ever had, with endless variety, top-quality ingredients, and views that made us want to linger for hours.\n\nAnother highlight was how easy it was to stroll into the charming village of Ascona, full of lakeside restaurants, shops, and stunning walks. It felt like an extension of the Eden Roc experience.\n\nThis was more than just a hotel stay ‚Äî it was a true retreat. Without a doubt, one of the best hotels we‚Äôve ever stayed at, and we can‚Äôt wait to come back.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"David Burke","rating":5,"text":"We stopped in for a private event and stayed for drinks on the patio afterwards.  What a beautiful location right on the lake with great views from the restaurants and patios.  Service was very attentive and efficient.  Drinks and appetizers are what you would expect from this caliber of property.  If we didn''t live a couple blocks away, this would be the place to stay when visiting Ascona!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"nooz s","rating":5,"text":"Quite possibly my new favorite hotel in the world.\nFrom the moment you enter it is an exceptional and magical experience. The lemon tree lined driveway leads you to a stunningly designed lobby, with views of the lake just on the other side of the beautiful stone terrace beckoning you. The entire property is dotted with jasmine trees, perfuming the terraces and lawns. The rooms, while snug, are beautifully designed. As usual in Europe the air conditioning could be better, but the trick was to close the storm blinds during the day which helped greatly.\nThere are three pools, as well as steps that lead directly into the lake. The breakfast was divine and with perfect execution and service. Every one of their restaurants had perfectly executed dishes, with tender fish pulled from the lake that day alongside seasonal vegetables and local herbs.\nThe staff was all incredibly kind and so helpful in every regard.\nCan‚Äôt wait to return","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Jddn Sndnf","rating":2,"text":"Beautiful location and nice staff, but very disappointed overall. The ‚ÄúAC‚Äù they advertise doesn‚Äôt work at all, and no fans are provided ‚Äî extremely uncomfortable. They also fail to mention when events like weddings are happening, which means restaurants, bars, and the dock were all closed during our stay. It would be nice if they were upfront about these things before booking.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"ex european","rating":1,"text":"I stayed here in 2019. I just had repatriated from California and most of my clothes etc were somewhere on the ocean.  I was not allowed in their cheapest restaurant because I had no sportscoat.  I lived in Calif and have gone to 3 michelin star restaurants where you can go in anything. Not here. Maitre D wouldnt have it. Not even after the GM of the hotel said I could eat there. INSANE.  They have a Michelin starred restaurant and I could have dinner there or in teh bar.  But not in the cheapest place they have because  the Maitre D''   wants sportscoats.  I had planned to stay there much longer, but I left early because of that.  I found another place with nice and friendly people. I hATE this hotel and will never ever go there or to there other locations. Stay Away","time":"5 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
