er with our stay, everything from the excellent boutique service, fantastic restaurants including an incredible breakfast buffet (many healthy options), a large kids club area, the pools, the proximity to Lake Maggiore.  They have a great selection of bikes to ride to the lake, which we couldn''t be more impressed with the activity and beauty of the lake.  And the housekeeping service was very kind and attentive, each day preparing the second bed for us morning and night. Wonderful stay!","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"P7 T6","rating":5,"text":"Our stay was exceptional in every way. The hospitality was flawless ‚Äî warm, attentive, and always respectful. We felt genuinely welcomed, and it was a pleasure to see that our dog was also kindly accepted and treated with care.\n\nThe highlight of our experience was without a doubt the food.\nWe had the chance to try both Ecco and The Hide, and each offered a unique experience:\n‚Ä¢\tEcco impressed us with its elegant, modern cuisine. The dishes were refined, well-balanced, and beautifully presented ‚Äî perfect for a relaxed yet high-quality dinner.\n‚Ä¢\tThe Hide, on the other hand, took us on a true gastronomic journey. Each course was a symphony of flavors, meticulously crafted and harmoniously paired. A creative, bold, and unforgettable dining experience. The level of precision and artistry in every bite was simply remarkable.\n\nThis hotel masters the art of hospitality and fine dining. A rare combination that makes it worth coming back to. Highly recommended.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"POSSOMHOUSE","rating":5,"text":"Probably one our favourite hotels in the world. The staff were amazing.  Food everything brilliant.  Gorgeous are to visit. Spa especially good.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
