 back.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Bintang A","rating":5,"text":"Absolutely loved everything about this resort! The staff was incredibly friendly, the rooms were spotless, and the views were breathtaking. The food at the restaurant was top-notch.\n\nThe spa at this resort is out of this world! I had the best wellness of my life followed by a relaxing session in the sauna. The staff made sure every detail was perfect. Will definitely be coming back!\n\nIf you want to focus on health and wellness during your vacation in Switzerland, this is the place to be.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Varun Mishra","rating":5,"text":"We had an unforgettable experience at the Grand Resort Bad Ragaz.\n\nStayed 4 nights with my wife and 4yr old daughter. Resort is impeccably clean, service is refined and the food is top notch. Their kids pool was great and entrance to the excellent Tamina therme was included. We just strolled from room to the baths in our bathrobes.\n\nRight from the moment of arrival when the valet picks up your bags to the time of exit, we were well taken care of. It was a relaxing holiday for us.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Lucy Sammons","rating":3,"text":"Lovely location, nice rooms and good spa facilities. Memories restaurant was OK - but very expensive for what it was.\nUnfortunately on checking out - and without advice - I was charged an additional ¬£133 (equiv 144 CHF) for simply settling my room bill in GBP. When I raised this - there was little support, suggestion of rectifying it.\nIt would have been helpful for this additional charge to be highlighted when paying the final bill - as it‚Äôs certainly meant my opinion of the hotel was negatively affected as a result.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"George Kowalski","rating":5,"text":"Luxurious and relaxing spa resort experience. Every meal was immaculate. The thermal spa and other spa amenities use local spring water that is fresher than any other water I‚Äôve ever encountered. Go out of 