ps://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/110784677607896955023\">H√¥tel Ch√¢teau de Fonscolombe - Relais &amp; Ch√¢teaux</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN245ykI2xRrpV61pO71R9241XolseWvO5kRnL78eI35iH-uBjwxEuVYKMW0FpHbXy8B7RxPGVjHEMifvzqI4Zr0iptRqJYIYX_vGkZZaI_nRIfaAcLUSVdLQigEvKozYUrRIorivW1rWLt1WhVEBAUweA-LbAwTpgk5N5btwtd9z6F7SAtC8PM0e5V-e9YfvD9sBJPFEzkHLRHeVfQg12nBgB7xbVZqBw41uOJhcxD_GtVnM37bFSTB2yGWljTlghgKltxUG4J9JVSwJpPMWwPflRg8iEzUcMjkdkKPm7hpZw","width":4500,"height":3375,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/110784677607896955023\">H√¥tel Ch√¢teau de Fonscolombe - Relais &amp; Ch√¢teaux</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0VzCbkojVceHnCEUz7y3tOSucwCY_LiUs0wHxjKVkS6eCKQGLhn6_kowuExX3QW4JSoriE0ZNM5aL0FxvqW5XdoQ_LFkGpABmgzI6NCuFVod6dB1uAXKN6BF8f0d_R6Xps0aKtylehIQ4oADn7GkT0oQ7Wc4KisPdHIEl4ByKHV2dU1kSTtGt7m2Q7NA8F-pCeoiiB3l-STbeZxTlSmPbeY_82bDEn5t8mTE9qmFaGhHSaRUffxJ1z6NznvVGFBINVOHdwiEPU0zXlQij2RIHgym-w1vmAEf4T_I5O7OZbvQ","width":4800,"height":3200,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/110784677607896955023\">H√¥tel Ch√¢teau de Fonscolombe - Relais &amp; Ch√¢teaux</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Hans Schmitz","rating":5,"text":"I spent New Year''s Eve at Ch√¢teau de Fonscolombe with family and it exceeded my expectations.\n\nThe ch√¢teau itself is an 18th-century beauty, and the grounds are absolutely stunning. Walking through the historic gardens with the chapel, you really feel the history of the place. Inside, the d√©cor strikes just the right balance‚Äîelegant and authentic without feeling stuffy or overdone. Our rooms were beautiful just like the public spaces which have been restored with taste and care.\n\nBut what really made our stay special was the staff. Everyone was professional yet warm, which isn''t always the case in today''s 5 star hotels. I have to give a special call out to Mademoiselle Juliette, who took care of us during the New Year''s Eve dinner at La Table de l''Orangerie. She was absolutely wonderful‚Äîattentive, charming, and made sure every detail of our evening was perfect.\n\nAs for the dinner itself, the chef and his team delivered a flawless performance. Every course was beautifully executed, and you could tell they put their heart into making it a memorable night for all the guests.\n\nIf you''re looking for a really special place to stay in Provence, I can''t recommend Ch√¢teau de Fonscolombe enough. It''s true hospitality with class.\n\nOne tip: As the public spaces of such a traditional building cannot be easily heated, think of a second layer for the colder months. The rooms were easy to heat though.\n\nLooking forward to coming back.","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Isabel","rating":5,"text":"This is my favorite hotel that I have ever stayed at, and I have stayed at hundreds of luxury of properties around the world. It was absolutely sublime. Walking into the grand old reception rooms felt like walking back in time, but with all the luxury amenities of a recently renovated 5 stay hotel. It was serene, peaceful, and absolutely gorgeous. I stayed here with my partner for a relaxing week of rest, wine, and reading by the pool. It has all the best that Provence can offer, including a Michelin star restaurant, but still feels like a hidden gem. I especially appreciated the thoughtful way the hotel was restored to leave as much history and charm intact. This was one of the best vacations of my life and I think of it often. 11 out of 10. A masterpiece. Maybe I will plan a wedding here. It was very romantic.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Jana Kirwel","rating":5,"text":"Probably the best hotel we‚Äôve ever stayed in. Staff was amazing: kind, helpful and always one step ahead of you to provide the best experience. The breakfast was delicious with mostly locally sourced foods. The hotels pledge to sustainability is visible in all aspects. Would 100% come back.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Heather J","rating":5,"text":"My husband and I stayed here for our wedding anniversy. Overall the experience was outstanding, from the moment we arrived until we left we had an amazing time. The property itself is beautiful, the rooms are well decorated and comfortable, the dinner at l‚ÄôOrangerie was incredible and the breakfast was well prepared. What really made our stay special was the staff. I had made a note in our reservation about our wedding anniversary and the staff went out of their way to make our celebration a memorable one. We plan to return in the future.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"M M","rating":5,"text":"I had the absolute pleasure of staying at Ch√¢teau de Fonscolombe for a week, and words hardly do justice to the experience. From the moment I arrived, I felt as though I had stepped into another world‚Äîone of elegance, tranquility, and genuine hospitality.\n\nThe grounds are nothing short of breathtaking: sprawling, lush, and perfectly maintained, offering a sense of peace and escape that is hard to find anywhere else. Walking among the massive cedar trees, I was transported back in time to my homeland, a deeply moving and grounding experience that made this estate feel even more special. Whether strolling through the gardens or relaxing by the 24/7 pool, I was surrounded by beauty at every turn.\n\nThe housekeeping team was flawless‚Äîmy room felt pristine and refreshed every single day, a true testament to their dedication and attention to detail.\n\nBut what truly set my stay apart was the incredible hospitality. Every staff member radiated warmth, professionalism, and a sincere desire to make my stay perfect. A special mention must go to Liticia, who went above and beyond for me on multiple occasions. She not only ensured that I was always comfortable but also personally helped me navigate stressful and costly rental car issues. Her care, foresight, and dedication quite literally saved me more than once‚Äîand I will be forever grateful for her kindness.\n\nEqually noteworthy was the classy touch of the manager personally reaching out to me, reinforcing that sense of being genuinely cared for and valued as a guest.\n\nThe 25/7 concierge service (yes, they truly feel like they never sleep!) was an invaluable luxury, always ready to assist with any request‚Äîno matter the hour. Combined with the estate‚Äôs timeless charm, ancient cedars, and flawless amenities, it created the feeling of having everything I could possibly need at my fingertips.\n\nOne note to the hotel: The food options are pricy and did not change during my stay, which I understand. But a rotating menu could help this for guests staying more than a week. The food was good, just over priced.\n\nIn short, Ch√¢teau de Fonscolombe is far more than a five-star hotel‚Äîit‚Äôs an experience, a sanctuary, and a memory I will treasure forever. If you are fortunate enough to stay here, you will be treated not just as a guest, but as family.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
