eARQy21bNtQmO4GPACnYUd-ABlZIpZMkQFXWwMr4y10WA-1KyT0Y4WJnfGGoxPmKeFlZa5gEFQZMnaw21bS7SgeqFw0z3Y5jQkA7zj3Gxq0XEmxtviQjE_v5lsZAWFD9Bqqkahe-AzH2JDRVnYbuvt9ulBWEkZUNuThHUKVjov2NQgEjGOSKZG0W0uFiBkoojl2_m3hq22EsRl2k2GRi4MBfPnqLqQWg","width":4800,"height":3200,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/118128403023624786118\">Ch√¢teau Les Crostes</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2kW6Zorq9eoaWU_vWUC2tpc0fu8KN6mJ_upw57zAAPBOzbAE3aSzfX2otci15g2FzYdZYWTrDOCgi1lzCBgkrZ618FChR7tfhECkSF4B5hC1ieBmX65bQObOgnP4eIS0JrvyPbAXeA-SBAggLlsxxhp6zu6YqZEk0pP7s94rBM2cfd7l8eg5TFcMqNaaTdmB7QJaSQ5zippcqK044IIEuVtHZ_JxwFfxYNp-H3xkvvydyNSIGEuyyhDsot7iZtkINwQ-bGUJOcbTuACl1oIji8xrCQ0vFVfod-ZM6jj3r8Tg","width":4800,"height":3200,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/118128403023624786118\">Ch√¢teau Les Crostes</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Chloe LOU JOIA STUDIO","rating":4,"text":"The property is in a beautiful location, with stunning garden landscaping and a lovely pool. The castle is impressively large, with charming ancient features that bring authenticity and character. We were warmly welcomed with a tour of the main areas of the castle and our room, which was a great start to our stay.\n\nAs an interior designer, I noticed a few areas that could be improved to elevate the guest experience. The paint on some walls is outdated and flaking, the kitchen feels old, and the towels had visible stains. Some of the sunbed covers were also dirty. Overall, the interiors felt a bit empty, lacking clearly defined zones and a distinctive design identity that would make the place truly special.\n\nI would recommend offering guests a glass of wine from the vineyard as part of the welcome experience, investing in modernizing the bathrooms, and adding thoughtful touches such as hand soap, extra pillows, quality toiletries, and some tasteful home staging in the rooms. These enhancements would bring warmth, comfort, and a sense of luxury that matches the beauty of the setting.\n\nOverall, we had a great stay, and a big thank you to the General Manager for the warm hospitality.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Kevin Lee","rating":5,"text":"We had an outstanding stay at the Chateau. The staff was wonderful and very friendly. The grounds are gorgeous. We made use of the pool and patio areas, all of which are great. The building itself is beautiful and all we could hope for in a countryside French chateau. Oh, and the wine? Delicious. We loved the Honesty Policy self-service given our irregular hours of coming and going. There are laundry and ironing appliances on site in case you need to refresh your wardrobe. Be sure to stroll the grounds and meet the different animals they keep, and swing by the winery building for a tasting and bottle purchase.\n\nWe will certainly be staying here again when we return to the South of France.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Hilary R.","rating":3,"text":"Someone should buy this hotel and turn it into a 5-star, as it''s got great bones, but needs investment.\n\nThe good: The staff were excellent (when you could find them -- it''s understaffed). The building itself and common areas are very nice. They are accommodating for pets. It''s set in a relaxing and beautiful nature park with tennis, a lake, and vineyards. It''s near a cute town with lots of restaurants but the good ones get booked up so make reservations!\n\nThe not-great: We were disappointed. It needs an influx of cash as it''s poorly maintained (flaking paint, etc). Most of the rooms could use a good interior decorator.\nThe water is non-potable so you have to go refill bottles in their kitchen.\nOur room had mold issues, wasn''t very clean, only two small bed pillows (we usually sleep with two each but couldn''t find any staff to get more), and the plumbing woke us with a grinding noise whenever other rooms used the bathroom. We could hear people walking above us, so make sure to be on the top floor.\n\nIt''s inconvenient that there''s no restaurant, not even a stocked minibar, even for snacks.\n\nNote to the hotel: I recommend that you add heavily stocked minibar to each room, clean up the pool area every few hours, repair the flaking paint and mold issues, add some no-chef snack options and serve drinks at the pool, and hire a decent interior decorator to make the rooms look more high-end (definitely not modern--go for classic Provencale... nature-tones, classic wallpaper and matching drapes would go a long way), repair the umbrellas, and explain exactly why the water isn''t drinkable (we were scared to even shower). If you do that, LMK and we''ll revisit!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Shannon Holland","rating":5,"text":"Chateau Les Crostes is perfect! It‚Äôs first of all an absolutely beautiful place. I couldn‚Äôt stop taking pictures, it was just gorgeous with every turn you took. The rooms were brand new and very clean and very comfortable. The pool was fantastic and the perfect temp and size. There is so much space on the property and so many places for R&R.  And the couple who run the Chateau are the nicest, most warm, helpful and welcoming host you will ever meet. They make you feel right at home! The breakfast is great as well! I seriously cannot recommend this place enough and I can‚Äôt wait to go back!\n\nP.S. the Rose they make is so good and I don‚Äôt even like Rose.","time":"2 years ago"},{"author":"Ed Tsvik","rating":5,"text":"What a beautiful Chateau!  We lived like a prince and princess for one night.  The property managers were great hosts and spoke English very well. A place we hope to visit again and spend more time at.","time":"a year ago"}]'::jsonb,
