, thoughtful gifts, and fresh flowers‚Äîsuch a beautiful and heartfelt touch. You can truly tell they think of every aspect of the stay.\n\nThe property was even more stunning in person‚Äîtruly magical.\n\nEve and Sebastian went above and beyond to make our time unforgettable. They helped us find exceptional chefs to cater our wedding dinner and shared thoughtful recommendations for local activities. They were also incredibly responsive throughout our stay, which made everything seamless.\n\nWe opted for the breakfast add-on, and it exceeded all expectations‚Äîabsolutely delicious!\n\nIf you‚Äôre thinking about hosting an elopement or wedding here, I highly recommend this venue! It was the trip of a lifetime, and we absolutely plan to return to the Domaine in the future.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Beno√Æt B.","rating":5,"text":"We hosted a seminar at Domaine de Lamanon and had an amazing time. The place is beautiful, peaceful, and perfect for a group getaway.\n\nThe private chef blew us away, every meal was fresh, flavorful, and beautifully prepared. Eve, who handled the wines and champagnes, made the dinners feel really special. You can tell she loves what she does.\n\nThe team took care of everything down to the smallest detail. We never had to worry about a thing. The jeep tour around the property was so fun and gave us a chance to really enjoy the surroundings.\n\nEven the logistics were smooth, from airport pickups to the packed lunches during our excursions.\n\nIt‚Äôs rare to find a place that combines great food, great people, and great organization like this. We left relaxed, happy, and already talking about when we could come back!","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Mariah","rating":5,"text":"When we pulled into this domaine, I was completely blown away. It truly felt like stepping into the movie A Good Year, a real Proven√ßal dream come to life. Everything, inside and out, was so authentically Proven√ßal and beautifully done. The interiors are filled with charming vintage pieces and thoughtful little touches (our room was called ‚ÄúCr√®me de la cr√®me‚Äù: how cute is that?). S√©bastien and Eve, the owners, are incredibly kind and welcoming, and between the wine, the gardens, and the beauty of the domaine, we honestly can‚Äôt wait to come back.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"allissa panayotopoulos","rating":5,"text":"Hosted our wedding here last month and it did not disappoint! Eve and Sebastian have executed this lovely domain flawlessly and are N absolute pleasure to work with. Will continue to rave about Domain de Lamanon and to also refer. Thank you so much for hosting an unforgettable 3 days x","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Vic de G.","rating":5,"text":"We had such a magical time at Lamanon''s castle! The estate is even more breathtaking in person than it appears in the photos. It''s huge and the atmosphere it exudes is truly incredible, there are a lot of different spots with a special vibes for each (i.e. a beautiful pool in between the vestiges of the old barn). The interior is also decorated with exquisite taste.\nOn the more practical side: Eve and Sebastien were always available whenever we needed it and we had everything in hand for our toddler and our baby (kids beds, huge playground, kids kitchen accessories, etc). Also a special shoot out for the A/C since it''s not always available in French countryside :) We will be back ","time":"a year ago"}]'::jsonb,
