kOPykUpeqZMSlS-_Grw6Y3OX4QQZlzZZQn5nNSt_lUNjRmANoM2rVLomdD6oh0_ag6lNyTq2yrCrdX_pXQpBnMsZK8L5Ebm0pcYIUIU2qjby0vI1Zl-B68xK2q9yZ01VzWU2PU4j462dYnnGx3oICRfHoPs7TmaxQWF4pUKmVueW6bg9aMWlPufNmY79urC9ljjf4IH5f6I_TP07gM7eSn-mMjYgFN5MKHkmDxaOoZ5B2SX0PbthQzCdlCTP-biwPCYuPTQLXIoEFipPMsg","width":4000,"height":2668,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/116651554800522405628\">Airelles Gordes, La Bastide</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN2DcOPmqY4ru0sGGxQls_99X8xZ7Dhcba-YT0reC1bOUldwQgJSBUNHvN72YWBUDnwkqDwp-9k_xb0ASseKTwvkDlCaUPFnglWk2pbKGaFwk1SowHsh-qDhzKYfkVyRqEZi7DMMS2zjDDZhGriuj34BLBiKCOfX-ZNqvS9xpCebdBdiGAHM_E7iTmCybNY1LDt34FUlmrUTmnxSj-lxHA3Nazye-ReqVJrl7-E_0mwe4x54ZbuLyYtiQhg9CgPSphuM8anWScTqoI03jENNmw6N7iIciu3RWCDFnD-n40kaXg","width":4800,"height":3200,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/116651554800522405628\">Airelles Gordes, La Bastide</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Tiffany Nevill","rating":5,"text":"We had a most magnificent stay at the Airelles Gordes location this fall. There are an extraordinary amount of staff at the resort that are quite attentive. Many of them speak English and we had no concerns with communication. The concierge was very helpful.\n\nThe small amount of rooms at the resort allows for feeling as though you have lots of space in common spaces and rarely feels crowded except during meal times. The breakfast buffet is most excellent. We dined at 3 of their 4 on site restaurants and had great experiences at all of them with Clover being our favorite.\n\nOur room was beautiful, themed to the local area with taste. Dyson hairdryer and Nespresso are always appreciated amenities as well as minibar items being included!  The gifts provided on arrival and turndown were lovely. Excellent housekeeping service was always provided as well.\n\nWe loved our stay here and hope to visit again in the future.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Savannah","rating":5,"text":"This is the most thoughtful and attentive hotel we‚Äôve ever stayed at. They even came into our room to deliver little gifts. The staff were all incredibly warm and welcoming, and when we were leaving, they gave us some snacks to enjoy on the road. Truly heartwarming and considerate.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Bella de Souza","rating":2,"text":"I really wanted to love this property as I have stayed at Le Grand Controle a few times and it is my favourite hotel. This stay, however, left much to be desired. The staff did not feel friendly or engaging, and I am sorry to say that they failed at making us feel special.\n\nIt was my birthday, and we had three rooms in the hotel. There was no special welcome, no bottle of wine or champagne on arrival for the special occasion. Which is fine, just not what you expect from an Airelles location. On the actual day, we had scheduled some of their picnic baskets ‚Äî I had to confirm my selection three times via email ‚Äî and we still received the wrong baskets with ingredients that some of my party are allergic to (!) which we only found out when we arrived at the picnic spot, of course. When I returned and pointed out their error, they did not seem that bothered, there was no follow up. Even worse, they still wanted to charge me for the baskets at check out and offered little in the way of apologies.\n\nFurthermore, there was a miscommunication (and again huge lack of follow up) about a birthday cake and my birthday dessert was some sort of sad peach concoction. Again, no sort of apologies whatsoever.\n\nAt check-out I brought up these issues and no senior member of staff seemed remotely concerned with the situation, since no one showed up to address it.\n\nThe property in itself is amazing but the staff just did not feel like it lived up to it. It felt like an average resort. We would not return.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Serena Lin","rating":5,"text":"The best hotel in our two-week South France trip. I love the impeccable taste in the hotel design and decor, the above and beyond 7-star services, the view from La Table restaurant during sunset is just dreamy. The Guerlain SPA is so relaxing and I adore the rustic chic vibe. We definitely will be back and we love Airelles brand ever more because of La Bastide. Well done!","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Adam Roberts","rating":5,"text":"Fantastic hotel. It''s very kitschy looking but smartly designed. The property itself is stunning with amazing pools and great views. Breakfast was really fantastic and had countless options. Dinners were decent. The only negative is the town of Gordes itself, which is overwhelmed with tourists and much less scenic than the towns to its east.","time":"6 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
