ps/contrib/110123751561803665231\">Grand-H√¥tel du Cap-Ferrat, A Four Seasons Hotel</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0Ws_6eSkQaA9RHjh3gPSKvkMjMLr-IT1S6KL8w56xj5qzXQZX-IC7ao3HFYhjnhE811BK-ZywhwVCgeFynL-2SiFKy9RgiFuLOmhWlGVhR2qO7IaxC83pXGVIYKpTi0Y3hmImuWfpy2f7GrOOHl3obc2N4l1Sv_L4dwfKqkIdCtGXlR0Ccig7vYI5q8SANXT5C5A5gEyv_aJj1FpYCB7WLPrzE1xAzuwyfTaotZQszi-RkePbRipPQAM9eoFeYHT-vySMMbc7uXZvxdunX31lrOzZKZxTAZCYcgZxS07g98Q","width":1983,"height":1115,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/110123751561803665231\">Grand-H√¥tel du Cap-Ferrat, A Four Seasons Hotel</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0pR9KoXIcx5kxPfAT_SdDmn89GCheWIxIyENEN1rYiyayPiv9L7urAwNGvqSQS66Z6IDXyouj3kbyDq1EK36MvzcDTA2Q2dS6lrhIfXPwtGWQJrUEPxNrPSKAdKtk-6qREUYyyclZujhd2Nruzop2MDkXOL_bM_9KYC0DIjY3yucUM5GDwt0s3ihRV8vVNOIeFXTxHTI4dB9poWz0O7B5B9j41CQE8LrIIsqdkeqwK1Bh5Z5fXkAU8wYTIf4n8Ix2gV2fBNmH7hRTYpl_hbJl0DrQHZZkkHS_2rayoqEOPMw","width":3199,"height":4800,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/110123751561803665231\">Grand-H√¥tel du Cap-Ferrat, A Four Seasons Hotel</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Matthew Oliver","rating":5,"text":"I cannot tell you how incredible and amazing Fourseasons Cap Ferrat is - I was lucky to have stayed a few times and we planned a wedding here too, and the service, staff, quality on everything was impeccable! Adele from events and Margaux from sales were absolutely catering, supportive and great to work with!\n\nThey even supported our couple a week before because there was a small problem, but they handled it super professionally and made everything easy!!\n\nI really cannot think of a better place to get married or have a beautiful vacation!!\n\nTHANK YOU TO THE ENTIRE TEAM xxx","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Sergiusz Napieralski","rating":5,"text":"What can I say ‚Äî the hotel is simply extraordinary. I‚Äôve stayed at almost all of the top hotels on the French Riviera, including Eden Roc and H√¥tel de Paris, and none of them even come close to Grand-H√¥tel du Cap-Ferrat.\n\nMy family and I have been returning guests every year since 2023, and as a true enthusiast of luxury hospitality, I remain deeply impressed by the level of service and the exceptional atmosphere that prevails even during the height of the season.\n\nLet‚Äôs start with the fact that the hotel is completely private ‚Äî without a reservation for a stay or a table, it‚Äôs simply not possible to enter. This guarantees full privacy, which nowadays is a real luxury (unlike at H√¥tel du Cap-Eden-Roc, where countless tourists come in and during my stay I honestly felt uncomfortable leaving my belongings by the pool). At the Grand, such situations are unthinkable ‚Äî the restaurant is separated from the pool area, and the staff ensures that only authorized guests are present by the pool. I always pay attention to such details because safety and peace of mind truly matter to me.\n\nThe reception team is absolutely delightful (as is the entire staff throughout the hotel). The spa team also left a lasting impression on me ‚Äî their dedication and passion go far beyond expectations. (Once again, thank you to the lady at the spa for the wonderful conversation about the hotel‚Äôs history and all the fascinating details!) The spa gardens are absolutely stunning and my second-favorite spot in the hotel, right after Club Dauphin. There are beds and loungers where you can perfectly unwind, enjoy a cup of tea, and savor fresh fruit.\n\nThe food is delicious, especially the breakfasts. The restaurant Le Cap is good, though I believe the indoor area could use some renovation. Unfortunately, during our visits, there was no wine pairing option available ‚Äî something that should always be present in a Michelin-starred restaurant. That said, the food itself was excellent, and the desserts by Pierre Jean were truly top-tier.\n\nIf I were to point out anything, I‚Äôd say that some rooms could benefit from a light refresh, and the spa‚Äôs pool area could also use a bit of updating. During our last stay in August 2025, the lift at Club Dauphin wasn‚Äôt working, which was a little disappointing since the view from it is spectacular ‚Äî but of course, technical issues do happen.\n\nThe service at Club Dauphin is also on another level. The staff by the pool and in the restaurant treat guests like family. I especially remember one of the pool attendants with whom I had a lovely conversation about the French Riviera ‚Äî she recommended visiting in October or November, and following her advice, I‚Äôll be returning to the Riviera next week for the first time outside of the summer season. One of my stops will, of course, be the Grand-H√¥tel du Cap-Ferrat ‚Äî and the forecast says the weather will be perfect! (Thank you again for the recommendation ‚Äî I hope I can thank you in person this time!)\n\nTo sum up, the hotel is like a fairytale. For anyone seeking the finest experience on the French Riviera, this is the only truly sensible choice. Nowhere else in the world do I feel as relaxed as I do here ‚Äî except perhaps at Amanpuri ‚Äî these two are my favorite hotels in the world.\n\nI usually never write reviews about the places I visit, but this hotel has left such a remarkable impression on me, and I‚Äôve grown so attached to it, that I felt I simply had to share my experience. I hope this helps those who are deciding between the completely overhyped Eden Roc and the serene oasis that is the Grand-H√¥tel du Cap-Ferrat.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Anthony DiCenzo","rating":3,"text":"I know this review may not resonate with everyone, but please understand the perspective: when I review a Four Seasons, I do so in comparison to other properties at the same level‚Äîboth within the Four Seasons group (I‚Äôm something of a Four Seasons ‚Äúgroupie,‚Äù often seeking them out when I travel) and among other top luxury hotels. With that in mind, this particular stay came as a disappointing surprise.\n\nWe had booked one of the highest room categories after a long transatlantic journey. At check-in, everything seemed standard‚Äîefficient enough, we were assured our room was ready. We were then escorted to a suite with a private pool. On paper, it sounded perfect. In reality, it was located at the very end of a bank of rooms, directly beside the hotel‚Äôs main driveway, front entrance courtyard, and next to the spa. The result was a constant lack of privacy and noticeable noise.\n\nI asked immediately for a different room, explaining the issue. The staff member told me this was the only one available. Too exhausted to check on other categories or options, we accepted it. Later, we found out that other suites in the same category were, in fact, available. That was deeply frustrating‚Äîand something we were reminded of every time we were in the room.\n\nThe broader issue: the hotel consistently met standards but never exceeded them. At Four Seasons, you expect more than ‚Äújust fine.‚Äù We never once saw management circulate to check in, nor did we receive proactive communication during our five-night stay. These touches are the hallmark of the brand, and their absence was glaring. The best way I can describe it: it felt like a paint-by-numbers hotel‚Äîthe framework was there, but the understanding, finesse, and color that bring it to life were missing.\n\nThe property itself is undeniably beautiful. The ambience is classic Riviera, with manicured gardens, elegant terraces, and a sense of history. The restaurants were excellent (I‚Äôll leave separate reviews for those), and the atmosphere at Club Dauphin was pleasant, though again it didn‚Äôt rise above expectations.\n\nFinal Verdict:\nFor many luxury travelers, the stay would seem perfectly fine. But for those who know the Four Seasons standard, this property doesn‚Äôt quite measure up. When asked in the post-stay survey if I would recommend it, my answer was no‚Äîthere are better Four Seasons hotels, and better luxury properties in this region.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Amna AAA","rating":1,"text":"The most shocking Fourseasons I‚Äôve ever been to.\nOh my god! Usually I LOVE the Fourseasons and stayed in many of them across the world. And usually what makes the Fourseasons so special is the exceptional service and staff members. But this was one of the worst hotels in terms of staff. They were the most obnoxious I‚Äôve ever seen. Not a hello not a welcome not even the door man doing his job by opening the door‚Ä¶. He deliberately left when he saw us so he wouldn‚Äôt do his job and open the door.  Luckily we do have hands and we can open the door ourselves.\nBut yikes the service and entire vibe of the hotel is just yuck.\nOn top of that the interior and hotel itself is VERY underwhelming and not as wonderful as other locations but that can be passed what cannot be passed is the rudeness of the staff.\n\nThankfully we are staying at the amazing maybourne riviera which is wonderful with AMAZING- exceptional service (which is usually what I find at other Fourseasons to be fair to the chain so I really ask that they look into their awful staff and management to rescue the reputation of the Fourseasons brand).\n\nI always had a statement ‚Äúyou will never find a hotel like the Fourseasons‚Äù due to my previous stays across the world but this one definitely changed the toneeee and disappointed and im never going to look at the Fourseasons the same again.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Matt","rating":4,"text":"The pool service was exceptional everybody was attentive and nice. The breakfast chef who walked around giving food was super nice and friendly. The complimentary shuttle service is very disappointing that it closes at 9PM. The grounds were spectacular. Rooms just fine. There are much nicer Four Seasons out there for half the price.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
