een, but Jonathan gave me a sense of trust and belief that words can‚Äôt fully capture. Throughout the planning process, despite the time difference, Jonathan and his entire team were always there for us. Their dedication and passion made the experience seamless, and I can honestly say it was the most relaxing and enjoyable wedding planning journey‚Äîeven without a wedding planner!\n\nThe first time I saw the castle in person was just a few days before our wedding, and it was even more breathtaking than I had imagined.\n\nOur three-day celebration was nothing short of magical, like something out of a fairy tale. The staff made us feel completely at home; nothing was too hard or impossible for them. Every single member of the team contributed to creating what we genuinely feel were the best three days of our lives. Our guests were equally enchanted‚Äîmany remarked that it was the most incredible wedding they had ever attended.\n\nTo any couple considering Ch√¢teau de Vallery, we cannot recommend it highly enough. If you‚Äôre on the fence, let this be your sign: book it. You will never regret it, and you‚Äôll come back to this review to thank me.\n\nTo the Ch√¢teau de Vallery team: Max and I owe you more than we could ever express. You made our dream wedding a reality, and there will never be enough words to convey how honored and blessed we feel to have celebrated the most monumental moments of our lives at your breathtaking venue.\n\nThank you for everything.\n\nWith love and gratitude,\nJennifer and Max","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Nour Dakir","rating":5,"text":"Incredibly STUNNING wedding venue. We could not have been happier with our 3 days at the Chateau for our wedding. Fabien was amazing. Helped us in every aspect! Worth his weight in gold and then some! The suppliers that are connected to the venue are second to none and very easy to deal with. If you are thinking of having a wedding in France, then you cannot go wrong with this amazing venue.\nThank you Chateau de Vallery for the memories you enabled us to create with our friends and loved ones!","time":"7 years ago"},{"author":"Katie Valovcin","rating":5,"text":"We first visited Chateau De Vallery digitally, Jonathan toured us around to every space, every room we fell in love and knew that this was the venue to have our wedding.\n\nWe locked in the venue before ever physically being there but the December before our April wedding we finally saw the property in person. We were floored. Better than we could have expected.\n\nThe staff at Ch√¢teau de Vallery are amazing, so attentive and really with us every step of the way\n\nOur wedding week at Ch√¢teau de Vallery was out of a fairy tale. We could not have imagined, better weather, better food, better company.\n\nThe possibilities are endless at the Ch√¢teau and it is really great you can house 60 people onsite. It is also only an hour and a half from Paris so quite convenient for international guests (which was most of our guests).\nWe loved all the spaces Ch√¢teau de Vallery provided. You could have a different party every day (and we did).\n\nWe cannot thank Ch√¢teau de Vallery, Patrice, Marie-Ange, Jonathan and all the team of the ch√¢teau enough. You guys made our dreams come true.\n\nDon''t hesitate to book this place. You will not regret it!","time":"3 years ago"},{"author":"Lucy Whittaker","rating":5,"text":"From start to finish and every step of the way; Chateau de Vallery was an enchanted fairytale dream come true.\n\nWe visited the Chateau as a potential wedding venue over 2 years ago and fell in love at first sight . . . every moment spent within its walls is  truly magnificent and believe me when I say the photos and videos do not do this incredible and unique venue justice. Our wedding was an event I never even dreamed possible because of this stunningly romantic venue and the absolutely fantastic team that run it. Our guests were truly enchanted by the Chateau and it''s eclectic mix of rooms and styles and it was so special to be able to host them while also ensuring the day ran seamlessly with the help of the team on the ground who were so kind and diligent and helpful in the run up to our big day.\n\nI cannot express in words how gorgeous this place is- anyone even considering hosting their wedding here should book immediately, it is one of a kind and I could literally cry tears of joy writing this review as it is just so beautiful.","time":"6 years ago"},{"author":"Christian Flouch","rating":5,"text":"Absolutely wonderful place to hold a wedding. Words cannot describe how magnificent this place is to hold the party of a lifetime. We got married in August 2019 and spent four days at the Chateau. Jonathan and the team looked after us extremely well from the first time we visited and right through to when we left for our honeymoon.","time":"6 years ago"}]'::jsonb,
