or":"Darrell Denner","rating":5,"text":"Ch√¢teau de Vaux-le-Vicomte is one of France‚Äôs most enchanting historic estates, and visiting it feels like stepping directly into a grand era of artistry, elegance and ambition. The ch√¢teau, created for Nicolas Fouquet in the 17th century, showcases the combined brilliance of architect Louis Le Vau, painter Charles Le Brun and landscape designer Andr√© Le N√¥tre ‚Äî the very trio who later shaped Versailles. From the moment you approach the estate, the symmetry and scale of the gardens create an unforgettable first impression. Every pathway, fountain and sculpted hedge feels designed to draw the eye deeper into the landscape.\n\nInside, the ch√¢teau is equally magnificent. The rooms are richly decorated, with ceilings, tapestries and furnishings that transport you into the height of French classical style. Each space tells a story, and the attention to detail is breathtaking. Highlights include the lavish Grand Salon, which opens onto panoramic views of the gardens.\n\nWhat makes Vaux-le-Vicomte truly memorable is its atmosphere ‚Äî less crowded than Versailles, more intimate, and wonderfully immersive. Evening candlelit events add even more magic, turning the entire estate into a glowing masterpiece. It‚Äôs a place where history, beauty and tranquillity blend perfectly, making it a must-visit for anyone exploring France‚Äôs cultural treasures.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Alex S","rating":5,"text":"great Christmas show in the ch√¢teau! we loved it! don''t miss the projection show! better buy tickets in advance. the hot wine in the ch√¢teau is worth to try too!","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Giselle Hernandez","rating":5,"text":"Beautiful chateau near Melun. Very informative exhibits about the design and ownership of the place. It was beautifully decorated for Christmas. Each room had themed Christmas trees and decorations, very festive.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Kimberly Whitlock","rating":5,"text":"Absolutely beautiful! With emersive headphones you can really imagine what life was like in the 1600s. We went in mid Sept and almost had the place to ourselves. Beautiful gardens. Highly recommend seeing this amazing chateau.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Katherine Sanford","rating":5,"text":"An absolute gem just outside Paris.\n\nBeautiful, peaceful, and exceptionally well run. The audio tour is phenomenal, engaging, easy to follow, and full of fascinating context that brings the ch√¢teau and its history to life. The staff are warm, professional, and clearly care about maintaining the property‚Äôs magic.\n\nIt feels like a hidden gem compared to the larger, more chaotic attractions. Take your time exploring the gardens, and don‚Äôt miss the rooftop views. They are breathtaking.\n\nHighly recommend for anyone looking for a truly enjoyable and well-managed cultural experience.","time":"2 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
