rything about the experience felt thoughtful and welcoming.\n\nThe food was outstanding, seasonal, beautifully prepared, and something we genuinely looked forward to each day. Just as memorable was the staff: warm, attentive, and incredibly kind. There‚Äôs a rare, familial atmosphere here that makes you feel less like a guest and more like you belong. Debora, Cecile and Alia especially were truly fantastic. The decor was great too.\n\nA calm, elegant place that truly invites you to slow down. We can‚Äôt wait to return.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Sorena Keihani","rating":5,"text":"I stayed here one night on my way back from Normandy. Really a nice and peaceful property with a lovely quiet garden. I did have a small issue with my room with some ladybugs and the staff were so helpful and lovely and offered me another room. Their on-site restaurant is also lovely and both dinner and breakfast fid not disappoint.\nThank you.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Ori Zieger","rating":5,"text":"We had an unforgettable experience at Les Chemins. Everything - from the exquisite flavors and artistic presentation to the warm and attentive service - was absolutely exceptional. We came to celebrate our engagement, and every moment felt magical. The atmosphere was elegant yet welcoming, the dishes were a true celebration of taste and craftsmanship, and the staff made us feel genuinely cared for. A perfect evening in every sense.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Christina Ashtary","rating":2,"text":"This place has definitely passed its expiration. I could only imagine it must‚Äôve been very nice at one point. The grounds are lovely and the rooms are ok, but there is no upkeep and everything is lacking. Service is spotty wherever you are whether it‚Äôs a restaurant or housekeeping. Little details like turn down service just being a flipping the bedsheet, a nice massive bath, but no bath salts or bubbles. Only Juice and Coca Cola in the mini bar.  But gym is atrocious. Weights with no number and broken cables on the sole machine that they have - it looks like no one‚Äôs been in there for 15 years. The Spa they advertise, has a sauna and steam room which admittedly were nice, but Jacuzzi and cold plunge and anything else advertised not in service. The ‚Äúpond‚Äù looks like a ghost town. Row boats half sunken and broken chairs.  There are nicer places you can pick on your stop in Normandy.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"James P","rating":3,"text":"All in all a very decent experience, but a few negative tones considering the price paid and quality expected:\n- The room was alright, but not exceptional. The floor was a bit dusty, so I had to wipe my feet when going to bed.\n- The Food was OK, nothing special. But the pricing was insane. I think I paid around 30‚Ç¨ for a burger which was average. There are no other options since it''s in the middle of the country side, so it seems they take advantage of this.\n- They charged me for water even though I asked for a \"carafe d''eau\" which means tap water. They serve bottles of water but I believe they are filtered, not mineral.\nThese are small details which is why I still gave 3 stars. But I found these aspects frustrating.\n- The rest of the stay was very pleasant. But for the price paid, things should be a bit more perfected.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
