to the history-laced grounds to the cozy and elegant rooms and the seasonal (and delicious!) dinners at Le Luce, we were repeatedly wowed with everything. We did drive to Le Mans to explore and loved its historic charm, but we were also eager to return back to the property to enjoy all it had to offer.\n\nThank you to Ludovic, Laurine, Bastien, Camille, and the rest of the wonderful team at the property who made this stay so magical. We can''t wait to return again.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Amy Owens","rating":5,"text":"I could not recommend higher. This stay was the highlight of my trip. The Team at Grand-Luc√® went above and beyond to make us feel welcome, pampered and waited on at every moment. The grounds are stunning. The Ch√†teau itself is beyond words. Thank you for making our Christmas so special.","time":"2 weeks ago"},{"author":"Eugenio Fausone Werling","rating":5,"text":"Everything was just perfect, from the very friendly and amazing staff to the stunning location and rooms.\nAutumn is a great time of the year to stay at the Chateau, the colours of the nature are amazing and there are only a few guests as it‚Äôs low season so the property is quiet and private.\nThe staff is the best note, always flexible and accommodating, with excellent attention to details.\nThe inside is just stunning, very well decorated with historical art everywhere you look.","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Jane C","rating":5,"text":"Wow. The kind of experience you really cannot compare or explain. We simply must plan another trip to bask in the grandeur of this historic treasure. Friendly, delicious, well serviced, great shower and room, incredible outstanding gardens and grounds, great reception and food. It''s very special. Beyond words.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Linan Qiu","rating":5,"text":"We did our wedding here in July 2025. Grand‚ÄëLuc√© is SURREAL. Photos don‚Äôt touch the scale of it ‚Äî gardens, limestone, that endless alley ‚Äî but what made it a 12/10 wasn‚Äôt the architecture, it was the people. The team was sprinting in July sun all weekend, flipping the top‚Äëof‚Äëthe‚Äëgarden ceremony into cocktail service, then resetting the central alley for dinner under the trees, cueing balcony fireworks, and finally turning the ballroom into a club‚Ä¶ and somehow doing it all with calm smiles. They fed us right after the ceremony (actual lifesavers), kept both sets of parents comfortable, and helped with accessibility needs without fanfare. Every transition looked easy on the outside because they did the heavy lifting behind the scenes ‚Äî moving furniture, tweaking lighting, checking sound, refreshing spaces at 1 a.m. and then again at sunrise. Our friends kept saying ‚Äúbest venue we‚Äôve ever seen‚Äù and also ‚Äúhow is this running so smoothly?‚Äù Same. If you care about hospitality and operations as much as pretty photos, this is the venue.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
