hor":"Christina Huynh","rating":4,"text":"Came here for a wedding, staying 3 nights. Beautiful chateau. The grounds are pretty with heated pool, bocce ball, giant chess, table tennis, etc. The pool was clean. There were trails in the forest that were very beautiful. The rooms were decent; we were in the Bonne soeur suite which included a living area with TV and kitchenette. They had shampoo and shower gel but no conditioner, but they left nice makeup wipes for us. Common rooms are cozy. The breakfast included was good. The sandwiches for lunch were also good but a little repetitive for two days in a row. There was iced/fruit infused water in the main area to use or potable water in the rooms. Staff were all very friendly. The wedding was beautiful, including a harpist and sabering champagne.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Nikki Bibbero","rating":5,"text":"As both a bride and the owner of an event management company, let me tell you: Ch√¢teau de Jalesnes surpassed every standard, every expectation, and every ounce of industry knowledge I brought with me. It was, without question, the perfect place to get married. The value is unbelievable ‚Äî far more affordable than a comparable U.S. venue ‚Äî and essentially all-inclusive. Our package covered the ceremony, reception, the majority of food and drink (yes‚Ä¶ including the bar), our cake, florals, live music, a champagne tower, and sleeping rooms for all our guests. It felt like a fairytale and a smart business decision.\n\nThe team went above and beyond for every single request. When I mentioned wanting mini golf during cocktail hour, the assistant manager‚Äôs stepdad literally built a full course just for us. When I dreamed up specific d√©cor details, Katy tracked it down and brought it to life. When my husband and his friends spontaneously wanted to golf the day before the wedding, David ‚Äî the owner ‚Äî coordinated the outing and transportation without hesitation. Fireworks? Easy. Special touches? Done. Whatever you can imagine, they‚Äôll help you create.\n\nAnd the beauty? My wedding photos look like they belong in Vogue, but that‚Äôs just the Chateau‚Äôs natural magic. Everywhere you turn is a perfect backdrop ‚Äî elegant, historic, impossibly romantic. The whole team is kind, thoughtful, and truly invested in making your experience unforgettable. It‚Äôs a family-run estate, complete with the sweetest resident pup, Bella, who made our stay even more charming.\n\nCh√¢teau de Jalesnes, thank you for giving us the most magical week of our lives. To any couple considering this venue: run, don‚Äôt walk, to secure your date here. Your fairytale awaits.","time":"a month ago"},{"author":"Leo van Noort","rating":5,"text":"Very nice to stay in a real chateau. Nice host and the swimming pool in great. The breakfast however is way overpriced .17 euros for a baguette and a croisant.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Aaron Emmitte","rating":5,"text":"My husband and I got married here a month ago, and words cannot describe how happy we were with the whole experience. From the location, to the food, to rooms, and the ch√¢teau grounds, everything about this place is perfect.\n\nFrom start to finish, the entire chateau team makes sure that planning your wedding is as easy and stress-free as possible. I''ve heard so many horror stories from friends over the years about how hard it was to plan a wedding, but with the Ch√¢teau de Jalesnes'' team that''s not at all the case.\n\nIf you''re even remotely considering a castle wedding, I highly recommend this one!","time":"8 months ago"},{"author":"Julia Hurley","rating":5,"text":"We cannot begin to thank Chateau de Jalesnes staff enough for helping us throw an amazing wedding in May 2024. The Chateau was a perfect venue for our intimate, elegant affair and from start to finish, working with the owners and coordinator was fantastic. All of the rooms felt homey yet sophisticated and the blend of old world architecture with updated comfortable guest suites made us and our guests feel like we were staying in a five star hotel that got to be ours for three days. We looked at a number of other venues in the area, and Chateau de Jalesnes not only had the space to accommodate all of our 46 guests (with a room or two to spare!) but they also had perfect facilities for the wedding inside and out, so in case of bad weather, we knew we would have a gorgeous wedding no matter what.\n\nThe wedding itself was simple and the Chateau and grounds provided a stunning backdrop! The food was exactly what you expect in France - incredible, local, and fresh. Dancing the night away in the chapel and sabering champagne were absolute highlights of our epic wedding.  Everything flowed seamlessly and it was actually a fun experience planning a wedding at Chateau de Jalesnes. The fact that they also have an in-house coordinator and a package that establishes your budget from the outset was a huge help planning a wedding from the U.S. We didn‚Äôt need to find a planner and they worked with us every step of the way taking care of anything we needed or wanted, and making our day absolutely perfect. People kept asking me if I was stressed about planning and I always replied that planning our wedding was the least stressful thing in my life!\n\nChateau de Jalesnes - the owners, staff, and Bella - will forever hold a special place in our hearts and we cannot wait to travel back to visit and stay for many anniversaries to come!","time":"a year ago"}]'::jsonb,
