ntrib/114302537896570448955\">Ch√¢teau de la Bourdaisi√®re</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN1HQ5Bzf-TQML3sxcB_Wxt950Ke2bFadvJFH9tsjeL6ZyI4mz0ULg4alB3IFpeqgAdwLwEKZYSHL7MA-kjPyix7n6mDkGKoswztfoEF7bd7s-ZLR6n6aHG3iX6K19Xf9kmZryE2J8REPWAISHs_UA9s6adW4O3vEEP04llvdbMEauUImdYKJ0uicCJNj9c41KvP-cHtC-ZohFypoxYfGH66LQ-mGxrj2wwX1GhDBIVawBkl3nYK62NPcZogoH-iliGnOLycy_KZZjQ0-jz8GdSRjxdtKj9VNdYmZH3r3F9EdP-OJH0BIao2yyFz0oVSa3G47Q9zTUf3NJTxx6Vb8MDFi6-a0l6vRpYKmqDNfpfnQLxOjs1SvCxhgkpjzlFJW5HERMO-mBJWotdH66rk06s5oLNmwyplFN_2M7MM9_KRdnrg","width":4032,"height":3024,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/100601336323723515825\">Pablo G Basso</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN3CT-Wpm_TcjYh9kgM0XQzlNmRC4cY_md4iSSIcn50txqkPHLI1h8pAG9cZHQmcpYAzBPFPpzMEgqlbT1Xgf7Xv9yiiyK_ksKIu8smSv4kWs2UfknDfzV2FSp1riFiKlfruMm_R3rbrc78wgd7VEtxH64CSR4EXVmUR7jjO-1vHlqQPIZQD4piRk8sqMdXFO9dQTHBIDmSAupJPZMOoYWZ6KfOqnruc6JMI_x1aKc4XXZB_vz5QKe5ojFySEz2OLddWuy27jx_tF5CYXWu48vOMQi608Xt-D_iYDVbWQ0DJ8QUWuclagCDiqC5OKWZ1fwSSPqRrIY81GA99QBy25Lg6U91SyBak7UMtsmROtKgW6vl1aBa_rl5qOzv2pkuFYe7R8-MT8264T2Ax92kq1vHAkk5hdFEm_OO5tTEIURTSfQ","width":2135,"height":2987,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/100214666394575485007\">Miklos Chudoba Balogh</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Shonavee Simpson","rating":5,"text":"Absolute stunner!\n\nThe chateau is absolute luxury and everything you expect when looking for a castle experience. The property is next level - the gardens are superb, the dahlias are so beautiful and the upkeep on the whole place is top notch.\n\nThe staff are wonderful - we had wonderful interactions with so many staff, especially Philipe! Everyone was so gracious and ready for a laugh, it made us feel at home.\n\nFood options are good (a lot of fresh produce), and Montlouis area is stunning to walk around.\n\nThis is an incredible experience all round, highly recommend for anyone looking for a castle stay in France - especially because it is close to Patis by train or car.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Agathes","rating":5,"text":"Magnificent Chateau with a wonderful collection of heritage tomatoes in the gounds.  Rooms were spacious and comfortable. The restaurant set outside in the grounds was fantastic. A simple set menu with produce from the garden, expertly prepared and served. One, if not the best, chateau we have stayed at.  Breakfast was equally superb.  Highly recommended","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Teji","rating":4,"text":"This Chateau is a big hotel. Rooms are traditional and hotel has tried to maintain its aesthetics. Decor and furnisyalso are traditional. Beds and Bathrooms are good. There''s nice view everywhere around. You may go for a walk anytime. Lots of parking here and many fruit trees in the parking area.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Matt palmgren","rating":4,"text":"We stayed here as part of a tour group.  Our room was in the annex which is the adjacent building.  The main building is amazing with lots of interesting items (caves, gardens, trails, exhibits, mini Eiffel Tower) on the grounds.  Have to say that this was one of the most memorable experiences of our tour.  This is not your average hotel, which can be a positive or a negative depending on your expectations.  It has some quirks (walk to room through the corridor could take a few minutes) but all in all we loved it.  Hard to beat staying on these beautiful grounds.  Breakfast was sufficient but wasn‚Äôt great. However we really enjoyed the dinner we had there (salmon)","time":"8 months ago"},{"author":"Alessandro Sorrentino","rating":3,"text":"This place has a lot of hit and misses. Great historical building that looks fantastic from the outside and might be quite charming from the inside as well, but it is not so well maintained . Rooms can be okay with some old change, but the bathrooms are in real need of an update. The garden and the forest are amazing, but the place gets almost dead in the evening, with no activity and it feels you are the only guest there. We wanted to try the tomato bar, but it was or completely booked or closed, so it did not work. In general the location is fantastic for a tour of the Loire castles, but it will need a bit more attention to ensure it reaches its full potential.","time":"a year ago"}]'::jsonb,
