at Ch√¢teau Rigaud was. From the very first moment, everything exceeded our expectations, and it turned out to be even more wonderful than we could have ever imagined. Every detail was so beautifully thought out, and yet the whole atmosphere felt warm, welcoming, and completely effortless ‚Äî it honestly felt like home, which meant the world to us.\nThe food was absolutely outstanding ‚Äî every single meal was incredible, and so many of our guests commented on how exceptional it was. Pictures cannot do justice to how beautiful this place is, but even more than that, it‚Äôs the people who make it truly extraordinary.\nOne thing I had been worried about was rain on the wedding day, as I really wanted to have the dinner outside. And of course, it rained ‚Äî but I don‚Äôt regret it for a single second. Having the dinner inside the barn turned out to be absolutely magical. It was so beautiful, cozy, and warm, and it created such a special atmosphere that we‚Äôll always treasure.\nAnna, the owner, is one of the kindest and most genuine people we‚Äôve ever met. She clearly loves what she does, going above and beyond to make sure everyone feels cared for. Her warmth and friendliness made the whole experience unforgettable.\nAlex, our wedding planner, was simply amazing. We connected with him instantly, and he made the entire planning process so easy and enjoyable ‚Äî it never felt like a chore. On the day itself, he ensured everything was perfect and allowed us to just relax and enjoy the moment.\nRob was also absolutely wonderful ‚Äî always making sure we weren‚Äôt missing a thing and looking after us with so much care and attention throughout the weekend. By the end, both Alex and Rob truly felt more like friends than just part of the team, and that‚Äôs something we‚Äôll treasure forever.\nLaura was incredible ‚Äî so professional and endlessly patient with me changing my mind about hair and makeup every five minutes üòä She made me feel completely comfortable and beautiful.\nJilly‚Äôs talent with flowers is extraordinary ‚Äî her knowledge and creativity meant the arrangements were not just decorations but true works of art.\nGodzi was an incredible bartender ‚Äî always making sure no one‚Äôs glass was ever empty and doing it all with such kindness and professionalism.\nThe entire Ch√¢teau Rigaud team was simply outstanding. Every single person contributed to making the weekend feel seamless, joyful, and filled with love. It wasn‚Äôt just a venue ‚Äî it was an experience that brought everyone together and made us feel like one big family.\nAll of our guests, without exception, told us it was the most beautiful wedding they had ever attended. We are beyond grateful to everyone at Ch√¢teau Rigaud for giving us the most magical wedding weekend, and we cannot wait to come back one day for one of the Escape Weekends.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Kelly-Marie Bancroft","rating":5,"text":"We have been blown away from start to finish with the venue and team at chateau Rigaud. Nothing is too much, the panning has been seamless, they offer a planning weekend which we found very helpful but also such a blast getting to know the staff and revisiting the venue. All of the staff have English as their first language so there wasn‚Äôt any difficulty with communication either.\nThey gave us the Pinterest worthy wedding I‚Äôve always dreamed of and the food is incredible. (That‚Äôs coming from someone that is a bit of a food snob.)\n\nThey made us feel so special and welcome, I cannot recommend highly enough.\n\nThanks so so much to you all!!!!","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Shelly O Connor","rating":5,"text":"I attended my nephews wedding here. What an amazing venue. The food was delicious, not to mention the wine! The staff were so professional, friendly,attentive & discreet.  The grounds of the Chateau are stunning. The ceremony was very emotional. We had live music with everyone up dancing all night. Highly recommend this place.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Rhino","rating":5,"text":"I recently came here for a wedding. All I can say is WOW!?! I stayed in one of the converted barns for three days. Very large comfortable beds with daily room service. The staff were fantastic, always attentive and friendly. The whole weekend was run incredibly smoothly, with seamless transitions from event to event. The food everyday was next level delicious. I could not fault anything about the Ch√¢teau. Highly recommended.","time":"a year ago"},{"author":"Alex Mart (alexmartphoto com)","rating":5,"text":"Ch√¢teau Rigaud is such a beautiful place. I was there as a wedding photographer, and it‚Äôs honestly one of the best venues I‚Äôve worked at. The ch√¢teau and the gardens are just stunning, and everything feels so warm and welcoming. It‚Äôs perfect for capturing special moments. The staff were super helpful too. Food - delicious. There''s a nice place for ceremony under the old tree right in front of the ch√¢teau, many beautiful areas to walk around. Vineyards ‚Äì perfect place for \"golden hour\" photos.","time":"11 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
