re helpful and happy to answer the endless questions we had about the castle, even despite our limited understanding of French. We were grateful to be welcomed to host our wedding, despite being foreigners. They were super flexible to provide a last-minute in-person tour of the ch√¢teau which aided us tremendously in planning the wedding.\n\nThe castle grounds are beautiful and well-kept. Ourselves and all of our guests were overjoyed to spend a few nights in this gorgeous setting. The rooms and bathrooms were clean, and plenty of blankets, sheets, towels, and toiletries were provided which eased the challenge of visiting from overseas. Natalia and Patrick were great hosts; allowing us to set up and utilize the space as we pleased for the wedding. We''re so grateful they allowed us to use any vendor we wished for catering, drinks, etc, as many wedding venues don''t allow such freedom.\n\nA few other reviews mention the prohibition of using the chapel for wedding ceremonies. Natalia and Patrick gave us fair warning of this in advance, telling us that we must get permission from the chapel''s priest in order to utilize the chapel space. They gave us the priest''s contact information and we were able to obtain his permission to use the chapel, which provided a picturesque setting for our wedding ceremony. This may not be the case for everyone, we felt fortunate to receive his permission as the French Catholic Church''s requirements are somewhat strict. We were prepared to host our wedding ceremony outdoors if we hadn''t gotten this approval.\n\nOverall, we''d highly recommend Ch√¢teau de Vitry-La-Ville to anyone, wether they''re hosting an unforgettable wedding or simply staying the night to experience the French countryside. We can''t explain how magical our wedding day felt here and are so thankful for Natalia and Patrick allowing us to use their Ch√¢teau for a day we''ll never forget!","time":"a week ago"},{"author":"Olivia Rose","rating":5,"text":"A Truly Wonderful Stay! ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê\n\nWe had an amazing experience staying at this beautiful chateau in France. From the moment we arrived, the hosts were incredibly friendly and welcoming, making us feel right at home.\n\nThe chateau itself is stunning ‚Äì spotlessly clean, tidy, and with a wonderfully homely atmosphere that made our stay so relaxing. Breakfast was a real highlight and a perfect example of a traditional French breakfast ‚Äì fresh, delicious, and beautifully presented.\n\nParking was safe and provided on site with plenty of space.\n\nThis is a truly special place to stay, and we would absolutely recommend it to anyone looking for an authentic and memorable French getaway.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Marijn de Wit","rating":5,"text":"We had such a perfect stay here, the castle is beautiful, the rooms spacious, and the host treats you like family. Wholeheartedly recommend spending a few nights here, while exploring the Champagne region. The castle is located in between √âpernay and Troyes, and Ch√¢lons-en-Champagne is also a surprisingly nice and friendly town with some very good restaurants.","time":"2 years ago"},{"author":"Miles Oldrey","rating":5,"text":"Stunning building. Fabulous proprietor who treats his guests like family. I look forward to returning for a longer stay","time":"7 years ago"},{"author":"David Rayer","rating":5,"text":"Beautiful rooms and grounds with a wonderful host. Brilliant.","time":"3 years ago"}]'::jsonb,
