dUq-I5TvubV-eVsubmnhgcb8WlcuGa8a4hKIIZBTON27uPE_vs5MpiYEjE3zlebpDMTJ-FgMzcy3eBfyvV6LtGrQAL3gi4Dl8m-xtFn2zzsg","width":1280,"height":800,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/110511352468884262662\">Domaine Les Cray√®res</a>"]},{"photo_reference":"AcnlKN0gwDexSPTRNty5mvvOZOzXHlu8R_BZyYKLtdowubwPSR2fjBTeTbcN9W8bOGlQPAeFpUxWUJxavbeE2-tYDEgefWdhkQCoNdckCtd9ynIlcm0djow_2_WzVdwQ4-XB_pjf5xnBNQ6eu71Q0r8hoLzxy_gI_I4Qc4vYamp8bvsA30Qi0EfJs5Rj3di4zaoIiXgF8HgIgE1sxCfI8IvrJ3LtKOFSoAFry_IEX2V4SzDDMoKdTs0Z6WC0jHqG3JYa0sjPal-WHNYF4f2UohxopDItz8g5DARjdPHqKDeBv9QiWg","width":1280,"height":800,"attributions":["<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps/contrib/110511352468884262662\">Domaine Les Cray√®res</a>"]}]'::jsonb, '[{"author":"Inte Wouters","rating":3,"text":"Last weekend, we spent one night at H√¥tel Les Cray√®res before continuing our journey to the Royal Champagne Hotel & Spa in √âpernay.\n\nThe welcome and service at Les Cray√®res were truly outstanding. From the moment we entered the estate until the moment we checked out, we were surrounded by a warm, attentive, and highly professional team. The staff truly deserve great praise for their hospitality and helpfulness.\n\nOur room was spacious, elegantly decorated, impeccably clean, and radiated the classic charm one would expect from a property like Les Cray√®res.\n\nUnfortunately, the breakfast did not meet the standard expected of a five-star hotel of this caliber. For ‚Ç¨100 for two people, we anticipated a refined and varied experience, but the offering was rather limited. Breakfast is not served in buffet style, which makes the selection quite restricted and inflexible.\n\nFor two guests, the breakfast included two croissants, two pastries, two chocolate breads, and a few pieces of baguette, accompanied by a small bowl of fruit and yogurt per person, plus the option to choose one egg dish. With the bread, only a selection of jams and one small piece of goat cheese per person were provided.\n\nAs neither of us are fond of sweet breakfast items, our options were very limited. Overall, it felt rather modest and did not match the price charged.\n\nThe atmosphere in the breakfast room was also somewhat disappointing. On a Sunday morning, only two other tables were occupied, there was no background music, and the room lacked the cozy and relaxed ambiance one would normally expect in a house of this standing.\n\nOur advice to the hotel would be to critically review the breakfast concept and perhaps take inspiration from other leading five-star hotels in the region. The current offering detracts from what is otherwise an exceptional experience at Les Cray√®res.\n\nIn summary: the staff and rooms are outstanding, but the breakfast clearly remains an area for improvement.","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Open Kloset By Karina","rating":5,"text":"The Charming Mystery of a Ch√¢teau üè∞\n\nOur experience at Domaine Les Cray√®res was absolutely incredible ‚Äî a perfect blend of French elegance, history, and warm hospitality. Nestled in Reims, this legendary five-star Relais & Ch√¢teaux property truly lives up to its reputation as one of the most beautiful hotels in the world.\n\nüè∞ A Ch√¢teau with Soul\nEach of the 20 rooms and suites, named after European royalty, radiates timeless charm and understated luxury. The attention to detail is exceptional ‚Äî from the elegant d√©cor to the indulgent Herm√®s and Guerlain amenities that make every moment feel special.\n\nüç¥ A Gourmand‚Äôs Paradise\nWe had the pleasure of dining at both of the Ch√¢teau‚Äôs restaurants, and each was a highlight of our stay:\n‚Ä¢ Le Parc ‚≠ê‚≠ê ‚Äì The two Michelin-starred restaurant by Chef @christophemoret_ was an unforgettable culinary experience ‚Äî every dish was art on a plate.\n‚Ä¢ Brasserie Le Jardin ‚Äì Perfect for a relaxed yet refined lunch, with an open kitchen and a beautiful terrace overlooking the gardens.\n\nFrom start to finish, our time at Domaine Les Cray√®res was pure magic ‚Äî impeccable service, exquisite dining, and a setting straight out of a dream. ‚ú®","time":"2 months ago"},{"author":"Christopher Cammack","rating":5,"text":"Whenever possible, I love to treat my bride to perfect luxury. So, when we had an opportunity to stay a night in Reims, Domaine Les Cray√®res was the obvious choice. This hotel excelled at everything‚Ä¶ the staff, the rooms, the lounge!!!  I wanted a perfect evening with my bride and Cray√®res delivered!","time":"3 weeks ago"},{"author":"Quinn M","rating":5,"text":"This was an incredible place to stay for our time in the Champagne region. Location is phenomenal with plenty of cellars and tastings to enjoy nearby in Reims but it was also easy to uber over to Epernay for more!\nHotel specific, from the moment we pulled into the gates to our departure, we felt welcomed and well taken care of. The terrace off the bar is gorgeous and our room was clean and comfortable, with a terrace of its own! (We splurged on the Ministerial Suite which I would definitely recommend, it was fab.)\nWe had dinner at each of the restaurants in the hotel and both were delicious and impressive experiences, especially at the Michelin starred Le Parc- 10/10 food, service and atmosphere.\n\n110% recommend. We are already planning our next trip to Reims and will absolutely be staying at Domaine Les Cray√®res again; literally can‚Äôt stay anywhere else after this beyond fantastic experience.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Kirk","rating":3,"text":"The property is very beautiful and picturesque. However, when paying over $800.00 per night, one would expect the room to be exquisite. Not that we use a minibar in a room but we wanted to use it to store some cheeses and meats during our stay. Upon opening the minbar, it smelled as if something had died in there. It was nauseating. The staff came to clean but it still had a foul smell. Upon returning from being out, we found the privacy blind on the main window had fallen off the support. The area rugs looked old and stained. The carpet in the bedroom was also very thin and stained. The bathroom and shower was very modern, stylish and up to date. We like to walk and enjoy the city‚Äôs when in Europe. This location was not convenient for visiting a local coffee shop, a local bar or selection of restaurants by walking. We loved the champagne region and will return, but never to Domaine Les Crayeres.","time":"4 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
