lamb(excellent) and the sardines (delicious).  You pick the protein and which sauce you want and either fries or salad.  We shared the fog tart and chocolate mousse (so French and chocolatey).  Defiantly would come here again and again.","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Sofia Crottogini","rating":5,"text":"The meat was good so with that they got my heart, also the price was fair as you pay the same for really bad meat in most restaurants that are in way less lovely environments. The atmosphere is perfect, the view, the dishes a 10. The bread and the cheese were also very good. People that complain about how fast things are do not realize that they are more like making you the favor to stay longer. Nevertheless, it''s also true that some things are irrationally expensive, the ricotta and vinegar ice cream was half of the price of the meat and it was just one ball and the taste... well, no comments. I strongly recommend the place.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"J Wynn","rating":5,"text":"La Dime was the perfect ending to our day. We loved the outdoor kitchen and the view from the terrace. Our food was delicious! The watermelon melon salad was sooo yummy! The steaks were perfectly cooked. We highly recommend and would definitely eat there again.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Daniel Schechter","rating":5,"text":"My wife and I stayed here for our anniversary.\nThe place is beautiful, the owners are lovely and the rooms are gorgeous and clean.\nThey‚Äôve converted a 12th century property into a work of art that blends design, architecture, minimalism and nature into a unique experience.","time":"3 years ago"},{"author":"lillian ghodsian","rating":5,"text":"What a hidden gem!! Heaven. Beautiful view, lovely drink, delicious fennel salad, vibey music.","time":"a year ago"}]'::jsonb,
