Friendly and very professional staff, excellent service.\nWe were lucky to get a wonderful room with old mural paintings and an extra small sitting room. We liked the huge bathroom with a stand-alone bathtub, no shower","time":"3 months ago"},{"author":"Somebody Someone","rating":4,"text":"If you are in the area and the weather is nice good for a coffee on the terrace or an apperetief. Do take into account appertief only served until 1745. And the wine although good is not necessarily worth the 16 euro (or tea the 8 euro) But the view is lovely","time":"4 months ago"},{"author":"Sergey Ishkhanov","rating":5,"text":"Historical country side French Chateau with beautiful area and mature. Excellent food, good service and kind staff","time":"7 months ago"},{"author":"Kevin Hinton","rating":4,"text":"Stunning scenery in a beautiful old castle but unfortunately the restaurant service was very disappointing.\n\nWe had a lovely room, that was dog friendly and our check in lady was great. Super comfy big bed, excellent shower and well looked after by the housekeeping team.\n\nThe Spa was very odd. No staff in the area, steam room was turned off and no changing room.\n\nThe dinner in the restaurant had really excellent cooking but the service was pretty bad. Had to constantly top up our own water and wine and the empty glasses and bread were left on the table until was asked for them to be removed. I asked for a dessert wine and was told ‚Äúit is finished‚Äù. Only after speaking to the manager did they bother to seek an alternative bottle.\n\nThe waitress dropped the bottle of red wine on the table and it was all a bit of a mess.\nWe felt there is very little training happening for service staff at this hotel. Also very disappointing was the lack of local area wines on their wine list. Only pushing the estate they own.\n\nOverall very pretty property but it needs a F&B service improvement, and support of more local wineries.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"A Holder","rating":5,"text":"I was lucky enough to stay for two nights at this amazing place.  As soon as you walk across the moat and enter the grounds from the carpark it feels like you are transported into another time.  Beautifully restored but still capturing the charm that only an 800 year old building can offer!  I was ushered into a room on the second floor overlooking the court yard, beautiful old beams and an amazing feel of the old wood lined roof.  I drank from silver cups and enjoyed the old oak cupboard nestled behind my bed.  All very charming.  The bathroom was quaint with a throne toilet and bidet.  No shower but a bath, I ended up showering in the pool area after a swim.  It was romantic and charming and utterly mesmerising to be there.\n\nThe gardens were superb, a cherry orchard and vineyards in the distance.  I was there in May so the weather was beautiful.\n\nI dined in the restaurant the first night with a limited menu which I was disappointed in as I wanted to do the full monty of culinary delights but needed to wait till night 2 where I was blown away by a delightfully entertaining 5 course meal including pigeon, which I had never tried before.  The breakfast was a served in the medieval atrium in the centre of the chateau and was a very relaxing experience.\n\nThere is a spa and pool area which I enjoyed using but spent most of my time either relaxing in the beautifully manicured gardens or enjoying my room which was large and had a sitting area.\n\nWhat can I say that but this is a unique experience that you must try at least once in your life.\n\nThe staff were very charming and accommodating.","time":"2 years ago"}]'::jsonb,
