ourself to an excellent meal.","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Lyudmila Emag","rating":5,"text":"We were traveling from Paris visiting Loire Valley castles. Chateau was our last stop before heading to Normandy. You really feel like a king staying there. The grounds are gorgeous, ground floor rooms feel like walking inside museums but then you can sit in luxiourius arm chairs, beautiful pictures are on every wall. My only comment is that breakfast wasn''t worth it. It wasn''t bad, but it shouldn''t cost 24 euro per person.","time":"8 months ago"},{"author":"Mike Hannah","rating":5,"text":"Rooms are exquisite, views amazing, this is five star luxury but four stars as possibly no bar (though excellent waiter service throughout grounds). Evening restaurant is also excellent, ‚Ç¨50 a head, good wine selection. Breakfast is a buffet and unless you get in early... Definately shall return when next in loire, we extended our stay this time. Highly recommend.","time":"8 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
