go"},{"author":"Victoria Onofrei","rating":5,"text":"This is one of those places that is too good to be true. The place is just amazing and the owners are very nice and knowledgeable.\nWe stayed in a cottage that was well equipped and really nicely decorated.\nThe breakfast is good and  the tables d‚Äôh√¥tes for dinner is a must as the food prepared by Stevan is amazing.\nThey have a pool with a stunning view over the vineyards.\nThank you to both Sven and Stevan for a wonderful stay.","time":"5 months ago"},{"author":"Tel","rating":5,"text":"what a fantastic find!\nSpotlessly clean room, beautiful pool in tranquil setting.\nWe had an evening meal cooked by Stevan which was delicious and a plentiful breakfast served by Sven.\nBoth Sven and Stevan were excellent Hosts with great attention to detail .\nWe look forward to a return visit for a longer stay.\nThank you!","time":"6 months ago"},{"author":"Joel Sadler","rating":5,"text":"This place was truly amazing. Sven and Stevan have done an incredible job of making this such a welcoming and wonderful getaway experience. We were travelling with 3 small children and a dog and came across Relais de Saint-Preuil by chance, and we were so incredibly glad we had. The rooms were wonderfully decorated and individually themed; the children''s bedroom especially which had three single beds in a long converted barn attic was amazing for them. We even stayed an extra night as we didn''t want to leave. The breakfast was superb and the walks around the property lovely. Given the time of year, they had made it particularly christmassy and that made it all the more special. I would even go as far as to say that booking the whole place for a large family Christmas getaway would be just as good as when visiting when the sun is shining, and we may even return for this. We accidentally left one of our children''s toys there and Sven went to the effort to mail it to us in the UK. Highly recommended!","time":"7 months ago"}]'::jsonb,
